list.item:
Fosaprepitant for injection 150 mg on Day 1 as an intravenous infusion over 20 to 30 minutes. (
                                 2.1
                              )

paragraph.content:
Recommended Dosage for Pediatric Patients (6 months to 17 years) Weighing at Least 6 kg (
                                 2.2
                              )

text.paragraph:
      See Table 7 and  Table 8 for a listing of potentially significant drug interactions [see 

                              Drug Interactions (7.1

                           ,


                                 7.2
                              ) 
                           ].

Coadministration of  fosaprepitant with warfarin, a CYP2C9 substrate, may result in a clinically significant decrease in the International Normalized Ratio (INR) of prothrombin time [see
                            

                              Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)

                           ].  Monitor the INR in patients on chronic warfarin therapy in the 2-week period, particularly at 7 to 10 days, following initiation of fosaprepitant with each chemotherapy cycle [see 
                                 Drug Interactions (7.1)

                              ].

tr.td:
Increased exposure to midazolam or other benzodiazepines metabolized via CYP3A4 (alprazolam, triazolam) may increase the risk of adverse reactions [see 
                                          Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)
                                       ].

Increased exposure of the chemotherapeutic agent may increase the risk of adverse reactions [see 
                                          Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)
                                       ].

No change in the exposure of the 5-HT3antagonist [see 
                                          Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)
                                       ].
